rooms.name: Abandoned Dining Hall
rooms.description: You step into the Abandoned Dining Hall, a vast vaulted space where long tables stretch into gloom and only a handful of splintered benches and an overturned candelabrum punctuate the emptiness. Dust motes drift through the weak light, the air tastes of stale wine and iron, and your footsteps return a hollow, patient echo beneath tattered banners that cling to the walls like faded promises.

rooms.name: Old Storage Room
rooms.description: You push open the iron-bound door into the Old Storage Room and a cool, dry breath of dust and rusted oil washes over you; the cavernous space yawns wide, its high ceiling swallowed by shadow. Sparse furnishings — a crooked shelf, a toppled trunk, a single chained crate — stand like hesitant witnesses, while your footsteps scatter motes of flour-dry dust and make the bare flagstones ring with lonely echoes.
